                  The National Energy Education Development Project promotes
                  an energy conscious and educated society by creating
                  effective networks of students, educators, business,
                  government and community leaders to design and deliver
                  objective, multi-sided energy education programs. NEED works
                  with energy companies, agencies and organizations to bring
                  balanced energy programs to the nation’s schools with a
                  focus on strong teacher professional development, timely and
                  balanced curriculum materials, signature program
                  capabilities and turn-key program management.
                </p>
