                <p>
                  Globally, forest cover is one-third less than what it once
                  was and global deforestation continues at 18 million
                  hectares per year. This indiscriminate felling of trees,
                  needs to be undertaken on a large scale to reverse the ill
                  effects of deforestation and restore the ecological balance.
                  In 2014-16, close to 1 million trees were planted by around
                  200,000 people, across 62 projects in 6 states of India.
                  Alongside, environmental education was provided to 180,000
                  children, teachers and community members. In 2019-20, nearly
                  161,139 saplings were planted across the country, while more
                  than 60,000 individuals were reached with climate literacy
                  and awareness activities.
                </p>
